'''Karauria Tiweka Anaru''' {{post-nominals|country=NZL|OBE|JP}} (2 June 1901&ndash;30 October 1977) was a New Zealand interpreter, law clerk, local politician and community leader. Of [[Māori people|Māori]] descent, he identified with the [[Te Whanau-a-Apanui]] [[iwi]]. He was born in [[Raukokore]], [[Bay of Plenty]], [[New Zealand]] on 2 June 1901.<ref name="DNZB Anaru">{{DNZB|title=Karauria Tiweka Anaru|first= Sidney Takimoana|last= Anaru|id=5a11|accessdate=10 February 2012}}</ref>
He was awarded the [[OBE]] in [[1957 Birthday Honours|1957]] for services to the Māori people.
