By 2000, there were at least five translations of the [[Tirukkural]] in [[Odia language|Odia]], all published after the 1970s.
==History of translations== The first translation of the Kural text in Odia appeared in 1978 by Chittaranjan Das. The list of Kural translations in Odia appears in the following table.
{| class="wikitable" |- !|No. ! Year ! Translator ! Title ! Location and Publisher ! Notes |- ||1 || 1978|| Chittaranjan Das || Kural [Oriya] || [[Bhubaneswar]]: Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan || Appeared in 154 pages. |- ||2 || 1985 || Kshirod Dash || Tirukkuralu || [[Sambalpur]]|| A translations in verse |- ||3 ||1992 || Nityanada Acharya || Tirukkural: Book of Sacred Couplets|| [[Balangir]], [[Odisha|Orissa]]: Agragami Karyalaya || Translated only the first two parts ([[Aram (Kural book)|Virtue]] and [[Porul (Kural book)|Wealth]]) |- ||4 ||1994 || Gananath Das || || [[Cuttack]]: Vidyapuri Publishers || Complete translation in verse. Based on the [[Tirukkural translations into Hindi|Hindi translation]] of Tirukkural by M. G. Venkatakrishnan |- ||5 || 1996 || Biswanath Misra || Tirukkural || [[Bhubaneswar]] || |}
G. N. Das's translation is based on the [[Tirukkural translations into Hindi|Hindi translation]] of the Tirukkural by M. G. Venkatakrishnan, and is also influenced by the [[Tirukkural translations into English|English translations]] by P. S. Sundaram and [[William Henry Drew (Christian missionary)|Drew]]–[[John Lazarus (Christian missionary)|Lazarus]] and [[Tirukkural translations into Sanskrit|Sanskrit translation]] by [[S. N. Sriramadesikan|S. N. Srirama Desikan]].<ref>{{cite book | last = Sundararajan | first = S. | author-link = | title = Foreword. In: ''Thirukkural in Oriya'' (G. N. Das, Trans.) | publisher = Vidyapuri | series = | volume = | edition = | date = 1997 | location = Cuttack | pages = vii | language = Odia | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref> Das retired from his IAS career in 1972, after which he took to studying saintly literatures, especially that of [[Kabir]].<ref name="OOCities_Oriya">{{cite web | url = http://www.oocities.org/nvkashraf/kur-trans/Ory-Int.htm | title = Thirukkural in Oriya | last = | first = | date = | website = OOCities | publisher = | access-date = 22 April 2017 | quote = }}</ref>
